ells, 1250\u20131513 |publisher=John Donald |location=Edinburgh |isbn=978-0-85976-631-9 |ref=B13 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Bridgland |first=N |year=2004 |chapter=The Medieval Church in Argyll |editor1-last=Omand |editor1-first=D |title=The Argyll Book |publisher=[[Birlinn Limited|Birlinn]] |location=Edinburgh |pages=85\u201393 |isbn=1-84158-253-0 |ref=B17 }}\n*{{cite journal |last=Broderick |first=G |year=2003 |title=Tynwald: A Manx Cult-Site and Institution of Pre-Scandinavian Origin? |url=http://dbweb.liv.ac.uk/manxstudies/sm/articles/gb.htm |url-status=dead |journal=Studeyrys Manninagh |issn=1478-1409 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207062510/http://dbweb.liv.ac.uk/manxstudies/sm/articles/gb.htm |archivedate=7 February 2009 |df=dmy-all |ref=B21 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Brown |first=M |authorlink=Michael Brown (historian) |year=2004 |title=The Wars of Scotland, 1214\u20131371 |series=The New Edinburgh History of Scotland |publisher=[[Edinburgh University Press]] |location=Edinburgh |isbn=0748612386 |ref=B4 }}\n*{{cite thesis |last=Butter |first=R |year=2007 |title=Cill- Names and Saints in Argyll: A Way Towards Understanding the Early Church in D\u00e1l Riata? |volume=1 |degree=PhD |url=http://theses.gla.ac.uk/4509/ |publisher=[[University of Glasgow]] |ref=B19 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Caldwell |first=DH |year=2016 |chapter=The Sea Power of the Western Isles of Scotland in the Late Medieval Period |editor1-last=Barrett |editor1-first=JH |editor2-last=Gibbon |editor2-first=SJ |title=Maritime Societies of the Viking and Medieval World |series=The Society for Medieval Archaeology Monograph |publisher=[[Routledge]] |location=Milton Park, Abingdon |pages=350\u2013368 |isbn=978-1-315-63075-5 |issn=0583-9106 |doi=10.4324/9781315630755 |ref=C11 }}\n*{{cite journal |last1=Caldwell |first1=DH |last2=Hall |first2=MA |last3=Wilkinson |first3=CM |year=2009 |title=The Lewis Hoard of Gaming Pieces: A Re-examination of Their Context, Meanings, Discovery and Manufacture |jo